<HEAD>Two Firefighters Killed Near Olympia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PIRGOS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two firefighters were killed Thursday
while battling a blaze in a pine forest near the site of ancient
Olympia, police said.
   ``They were ahead of everybody else with a hose when the fire
outflanked them and just swallowed them up,'' an officer said in a
telephone interview from the nearby town of Pirgos, 195 miles west
of Athens.
   Forestry officials were unable to estimate the damage to the
forest of Palaiovarvassaina because the fire was still raging and
was fanned by strong wind, the officer said on condition of
anonymity.
   Olympia, a sanctuary that was the site of the ancient Olympic
Games founded in the eighth century B.C., is located in lush pine
forests in the western Peloponnesos peninsula.
   Excavations have revealed part of the temple of Zeus, one of the
seven wonders of the ancient world.
</TEXT>
